Error: Error: "The Allocated RAM For Your Minecraft Server Is Not Enough And The Server Crashes Frequently."

Solution: Step 1: Log in to your Pterodactyl panel.
Step 2: Click on the server you want to allocate more RAM.
Step 3: Click on the "Console" tab and stop the server.
Step 4: Click on the "File Manager" tab and then navigate to the "Server Properties" file. 
Step 5: Open the "Server Properties
